      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p><i>N</i>,<i>N</i>-Diethyl-<i>m</i>-toluamide (DEET) is the active ingredient in many insect-repellent preparations. How might you synthesize this substance from <i>m</i>-bromotoluene?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBazBYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--3d021dcc6d2b8057da60a2201599981ebd321066/OChem_21_EC_054.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of N, N-diethyl-m-toluamide comrpises of a benzene ring with a carbonyl carbon attached and a methyl group in the meta position. The carbonyl group is also attached to a diethylamine group.\">",
